The '''Melanesian Progressive Union''' ({{lang-fr|Union progressiste mélanésienne}}, UPM) is a [[militant]] [[Socialism|socialist]] [[Secession|pro-independence]] [[political party]] in [[New Caledonia]]. It is a component of the [[National Union for Independence]], which in turn is one of the two components of the [[Kanak Socialist National Liberation Front]] (FLNKS).

==History==

The UPM was founded in 1974 by [[Melanesian]] supporters of the [[Caledonian Union]] who were opposed to the leader of the party, the white Maurice Lenormand. At first a [[Trotskyist]] political party close to the [[Revolutionary Communist League (France)|LCR]] in [[France]], the party has since moderated to become a [[social democratic]] party. 
